items.title: You Can Name Your Kid “'American Pie,' But Not 'Nutella'? Here's 11 Baby Names Banned in the U.S.
items.description: America: where you can buy a flamethrower at Walmart but can’t name your baby 'Santa Claus'. Turns out there’s an official list of 11 baby names that have been straight-up banned by U.S. courts, and no, it’s not just the ones you'd expect. For example, III is on the list. (although I'm not sure if that means '3', or i i i, but either way, I guess that means II or IV is okay). Some are bizarre, some are hilarious, and a few will make you question everything. Go ahead and see for yourself.

items.title: Amazon's Giving Out Gas Discounts This Month: Here's the 27 steps needed to redeem
items.description: Okay, so maybe not quite 27 steps, but It's definatley not just one. Prime members can save 20 cents a gallon this month, on Fridays, after signing up for a program called earnify, after linking your earnify and Amazon account. After downloading the earnify app. After using the app to find participating BP, Amoco, and AM/PM stations. So, is it Friday yet? Guess I'll push the car around until then. All the details can be found below.
